    Performs Canonical Correlation Analysis using Empirical Orthogonal Functions from a lagged dataset using a stars object

    cancor_eof.stars.Rd

    Performs CCA using EOF analysis using a stars object

    Usage

    # S3 method for stars
cancor_eof(x, lag = 7, n_eof = 10, ...)

    Arguments

    x

    The dataframe or stars object. If it is a dataframe, then it should have the locations.

    lag

    Specifies the lag to be used.

    n_eof

    The number of EOFs to be used.

    ...

    Other arguments that need to be used for datafames or currently ignored.

    Examples

    library(dplyr)
